  "cells": [
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "# Question 3: Carvana Image Masking – U-Net Training & Evaluation\n",
        "\n",
        "**Dataset:** [Kaggle Carvana Image Masking Challenge](https://www.kaggle.com/c/carvana-image-masking-challenge/data)  \n",
        "**Task:** Binary segmentation (car vs background)  \n",
        "**Split:** 1000 images total (800 train, 200 test)\n",
        "\n",
        "## Part (a) – U-Net from scratch\n",
        "- Encoder: 4 downsampling blocks (conv–conv–maxpool)\n",
        "- Bottleneck: central layer\n",
        "- Decoder: 4 upsampling blocks with skip connections\n",
        "- Loss: BCE + Dice | Optimizer: Adam + LR schedule | Augmentation: rotation, flip, brightness, contrast\n",
        "- Train 30 epochs → plot train/val loss and IoU\n",
        "- Eval: IoU, Dice, Pixel Accuracy | 10 prediction figures | 3 worst-prediction error analysis\n",
        "\n",
        "## Part (b) – Transfer learning (placeholder)\n",
        "\n",
        "---\n",
        "\n",
        "**Setup:** Download the competition data from Kaggle and set `CARVANA_ROOT` below to the folder containing `train/` and `train_masks/`."
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "execution_count": null,
      "metadata": {},
      "outputs": [],
      "source": [
        "!pip install torch torchvision numpy matplotlib pillow scikit-image tqdm --quiet"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "execution_count": null,
      "metadata": {},
      "outputs": [],
      "source": [
        "import os\n",
        "import random\n",
        "import numpy as np\n",
        "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
        "from pathlib import Path\n",
        "from PIL import Image\n",
        "import torch\n",
        "import torch.nn as nn\n",
        "import torch.nn.functional as F\n",
        "from torch.utils.data import Dataset, DataLoader\n",
        "from torch.optim.lr_scheduler import CosineAnnealingLR\n",
        "from tqdm import tqdm\n",
        "\n",
        "np.random.seed(42)\n",
        "torch.manual_seed(42)\n",
        "plt.rcParams['figure.figsize'] = (10, 6)"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "## Data path and config\n",
        "\n",
        "Point `CARVANA_ROOT` to the folder that contains `train/` (images) and `train_masks/` (masks).  
        "After downloading from Kaggle you may have e.g. `train.zip` and `train_masks.zip` – unzip so that:\n",
        "- `CARVANA_ROOT/train/*.jpg`\n",
        "- `CARVANA_ROOT/train_masks/*.gif` (or `*_mask.png`)\n",
        "Mask filenames often match image names with `_mask` before the extension (e.g. `id_01.jpg` → `id_01_mask.gif`)."
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "execution_count": null,
      "metadata": {},
      "outputs": [],
      "source": [
        "CARVANA_ROOT = Path(r'C:\\Users\\arzoo\\Downloads\\carvana-image-masking-challenge')  # change to your path\n",
        "TRAIN_IMG_DIR = CARVANA_ROOT / 'train'\n",
        "TRAIN_MASK_DIR = CARVANA_ROOT / 'train_masks'\n",
        "\n",
        "N_TRAIN = 800\n",
        "N_TEST = 200\n",
        "IMG_SIZE = 256\n",
        "BATCH_SIZE = 16\n",
        "EPOCHS = 30\n",
        "LR = 1e-3\n",
        "DEVICE = torch.device('cuda' if torch.cuda.is_available() else 'cpu')\n",
        "print('Device:', DEVICE)\n",
        "print('Train dir exists:', TRAIN_IMG_DIR.exists())\n",
        "print('Masks dir exists:', TRAIN_MASK_DIR.exists())"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "## Dataset and augmentation\n",
        "\n",
        "We build a list of (image, mask) pairs from the training set, then split into 800 train / 200 test.  
        "Augmentation: rotation, horizontal flip, brightness, contrast."
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "execution_count": null,
      "metadata": {},
      "outputs": [],
      "source": [
        "def find_image_mask_pairs(img_dir, mask_dir):\n",
        "    pairs = []\n",
        "    if not img_dir.exists():\n",
        "        return pairs\n",
        "    for p in sorted(img_dir.glob('*.jpg')):\n",
        "        stem = p.stem\n",
        "        # Carvana: mask can be stem_mask.gif or stem.gif in train_masks\n",
        "        for ext in ['_mask.gif', '_mask.png', '.gif', '.png']:\n",
        "            m = mask_dir / (stem + ext)\n",
        "            if m.exists():\n",
        "                pairs.append((str(p), str(m)))\n",
        "                break\n",
        "    return pairs\n",
        "\n",
        "\n",
        "class CarvanaDataset(Dataset):\n",
        "    def __init__(self, pairs, size=256, augment=False):\n",
        "        self.pairs = pairs\n",
        "        self.size = size\n",
        "        self.augment = augment\n",
        "\n",
        "    def __len__(self):\n",
        "        return len(self.pairs)\n",
        "\n",
        "    def __getitem__(self, i):\n",
        "        img_path, mask_path = self.pairs[i]\n",
        "        img = np.array(Image.open(img_path).convert('RGB'))\n",
        "        mask = np.array(Image.open(mask_path))\n",
        "        if mask.ndim == 3:\n",
        "            mask = mask[:, :, 0]\n",
        "        mask = (mask > 0).astype(np.float32)\n",
        "\n",
        "        # Resize\n",
        "        from PIL import Image as PILImage\n",
        "        img = np.array(PILImage.fromarray(img).resize((self.size, self.size)))\n",
        "        mask = np.array(PILImage.fromarray((mask * 255).astype(np.uint8)).resize((self.size, self.size), PILImage.NEAREST)) / 255.0\n",
        "\n",
        "        if self.augment:\n",
        "            # Random rotation (0, 90, 180, 270)\n",
        "            k = random.randint(0, 3)\n",
        "            img = np.rot90(img, k).copy()\n",
        "            mask = np.rot90(mask, k).copy()\n",
        "            # Random horizontal flip\n",
        "            if random.random() > 0.5:\n",
        "                img = np.fliplr(img).copy()\n",
        "                mask = np.fliplr(mask).copy()\n",
        "            # Brightness & contrast (scale and shift)\n",
        "            b, c = random.uniform(0.8, 1.2), random.uniform(0.8, 1.2)\n",
        "            img = np.clip(img.astype(np.float32) * c + (b - 1) * 128, 0, 255).astype(np.uint8)\n",
        "\n",
        "        img = torch.from_numpy(img).permute(2, 0, 1).float() / 255.0\n",
        "        mask = torch.from_numpy(mask).unsqueeze(0).float()\n",
        "        return img, mask"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "execution_count": null,
      "metadata": {},
      "outputs": [],
      "source": [
        "all_pairs = find_image_mask_pairs(TRAIN_IMG_DIR, TRAIN_MASK_DIR)\n",
        "print('Total image-mask pairs found:', len(all_pairs))\n",
        "if len(all_pairs) < N_TRAIN + N_TEST:\n",
        "    raise RuntimeError('Need at least %d pairs; found %d. Check CARVANA_ROOT and train/train_masks.' % (N_TRAIN + N_TEST, len(all_pairs)))\n",
        "random.Random(42).shuffle(all_pairs)\n",
        "train_pairs = all_pairs[:N_TRAIN]\n",
        "test_pairs = all_pairs[N_TRAIN:N_TRAIN + N_TEST]\n",
        "\n",
        "train_ds = CarvanaDataset(train_pairs, size=IMG_SIZE, augment=True)\n",
        "test_ds = CarvanaDataset(test_pairs, size=IMG_SIZE, augment=False)\n",
        "train_loader = DataLoader(train_ds, batch_size=BATCH_SIZE, shuffle=True, num_workers=0, pin_memory=True)\n",
        "test_loader = DataLoader(test_ds, batch_size=BATCH_SIZE, shuffle=False)\n",
        "print('Train batches:', len(train_loader), '| Test batches:', len(test_loader))"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "## U-Net implementation\n",
        "\n",
        "- **Encoder:** 4 blocks, each (conv 3×3 → conv 3×3 → maxpool).\n",
        "- **Bottleneck:** conv block at lowest resolution.\n",
        "- **Decoder:** 4 blocks with upsample + skip from encoder; each block two convs.\n",
        "- **Output:** 1×1 conv → binary mask."
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "execution_count": null,
      "metadata": {},
      "outputs": [],
      "source": [
        "class DoubleConv(nn.Module):\n",
        "    def __init__(self, in_ch, out_ch):\n",
        "        super().__init__()\n",
        "        self.conv = nn.Sequential(\n",
        "            nn.Conv2d(in_ch, out_ch, 3, padding=1),\n",
        "            nn.BatchNorm2d(out_ch),\n",
        "            nn.ReLU(inplace=True),\n",
        "            nn.Conv2d(out_ch, out_ch, 3, padding=1),\n",
        "            nn.BatchNorm2d(out_ch),\n",
        "            nn.ReLU(inplace=True),\n",
        "        )\n",
        "\n",
        "    def forward(self, x):\n",
        "        return self.conv(x)\n",
        "\n",
        "\n",
        "class DownBlock(nn.Module):\n",
        "    \"\"\"Encoder block: conv-conv-maxpool (as per spec).\"\"\"\n",
        "    def __init__(self, in_ch, out_ch):\n",
        "        super().__init__()\n",
        "        self.conv = DoubleConv(in_ch, out_ch)\n",
        "        self.pool = nn.MaxPool2d(2)\n",
        "\n",
        "    def forward(self, x):\n",
        "        return self.pool(self.conv(x))\n",
        "\n",
        "\n",
        "class UpBlock(nn.Module):\n",
        "    def __init__(self, in_ch, out_ch):\n",
        "        super().__init__()\n",
        "        self.up = nn.ConvTranspose2d(in_ch, in_ch // 2, 2, stride=2)\n",
        "        self.conv = DoubleConv(in_ch, out_ch)\n",
        "\n",
        "    def forward(self, x, skip):\n",
        "        x = self.up(x)\n",
        "        if skip.shape[2:] != x.shape[2:]:\n",
        "            skip = F.interpolate(skip, size=x.shape[2:], mode='bilinear', align_corners=False)\n",
        "        x = torch.cat([skip, x], dim=1)\n",
        "        return self.conv(x)\n",
        "\n",
        "\n",
        "class UNet(nn.Module):\n",
        "    def __init__(self, in_ch=3, out_ch=1):\n",
        "        super().__init__()\n",
        "        # Encoder: 4 downsampling blocks (conv-conv-maxpool)\n",
        "        self.enc1 = DownBlock(in_ch, 64)    # 256 -> 128\n",
        "        self.enc2 = DownBlock(64, 128)      # 128 -> 64\n",
        "        self.enc3 = DownBlock(128, 256)    # 64 -> 32\n",
        "        self.enc4 = DownBlock(256, 512)    # 32 -> 16\n",
        "        self.bottleneck = DoubleConv(512, 1024)  # central layer, 16x16\n",
        "        # Decoder: 4 upsampling blocks with skip connections\n",
        "        self.up4 = UpBlock(1024, 512)\n",
        "        self.up3 = UpBlock(512, 256)\n",
        "        self.up2 = UpBlock(256, 128)\n",
        "        self.up1 = UpBlock(128, 64)\n",
        "        self.out = nn.Conv2d(64, out_ch, 1)\n",
        "\n",
        "    def forward(self, x):\n",
        "        e1 = self.enc1(x)      # 128\n",
        "        e2 = self.enc2(e1)     # 64\n",
        "        e3 = self.enc3(e2)    # 32\n",
        "        e4 = self.enc4(e3)    # 16\n",
        "        b = self.bottleneck(e4)\n",
        "        d4 = self.up4(b, e4)\n",
        "        d3 = self.up3(d4, e3)\n",
        "        d2 = self.up2(d3, e2)\n",
        "        d1 = self.up1(d2, e1)\n",
        "        return self.out(d1)"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "## Loss: BCE + Dice"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "execution_count": null,
      "metadata": {},
      "outputs": [],
      "source": [
        "def dice_loss(pred, target, smooth=1.0):\n",
        "    pred = pred.view(-1)\n",
        "    target = target.view(-1)\n",
        "    inter = (pred * target).sum()\n",
        "    union = pred.sum() + target.sum()\n",
        "    dice = (2 * inter + smooth) / (union + smooth)\n",
        "    return 1 - dice\n",
        "\n",
        "\n",
        "def combined_loss(pred, target):\n",
        "    bce = F.binary_cross_entropy_with_logits(pred, target)\n",
        "    pred_sigm = torch.sigmoid(pred)\n",
        "    d = dice_loss(pred_sigm, target)\n",
        "    return bce + d"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "## Training loop (30 epochs, Adam, LR schedule)\n",
        "\n",
        "We record train/val loss and validation IoU per epoch, then plot curves."
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "execution_count": null,
      "metadata": {},
      "outputs": [],
      "source": [
        "def iou_batch(pred_logits, target, thresh=0.5):\n",
        "    pred = (torch.sigmoid(pred_logits) > thresh).float()\n",
        "    inter = (pred * target).sum(dim=(1,2,3))\n",
        "    union = pred.sum(dim=(1,2,3)) + target.sum(dim=(1,2,3)) - inter\n",
        "    iou = (inter + 1e-8) / (union + 1e-8)\n",
        "    return iou.mean().item()\n",
        "\n",
        "\n",
        "model = UNet(3, 1).to(DEVICE)\n",
        "opt = torch.optim.Adam(model.parameters(), lr=LR)\n",
        "scheduler = CosineAnnealingLR(opt, T_max=EPOCHS)\n",
        "\n",
        "hist = {'train_loss': [], 'val_loss': [], 'val_iou': []}\n",
        "\n",
        "for epoch in range(EPOCHS):\n",
        "    model.train()\n",
        "    train_loss = 0.0\n",
        "    for img, mask in tqdm(train_loader, desc='Train', leave=False):\n",
        "        img, mask = img.to(DEVICE), mask.to(DEVICE)\n",
        "        opt.zero_grad()\n",
        "        out = model(img)\n",
        "        loss = combined_loss(out, mask)\n",
        "        loss.backward()\n",
        "        opt.step()\n",
        "        train_loss += loss.item()\n",
        "    scheduler.step()\n",
        "    train_loss /= len(train_loader)\n",
        "    hist['train_loss'].append(train_loss)\n",
        "\n",
        "    model.eval()\n",
        "    val_loss = 0.0\n",
        "    val_iou_sum = 0.0\n",
        "    with torch.no_grad():\n",
        "        for img, mask in test_loader:\n",
        "            img, mask = img.to(DEVICE), mask.to(DEVICE)\n",
        "            out = model(img)\n",
        "            val_loss += combined_loss(out, mask).item()\n",
        "            val_iou_sum += iou_batch(out, mask)\n",
        "    val_loss /= len(test_loader)\n",
        "    val_iou_sum /= len(test_loader)\n",
        "    hist['val_loss'].append(val_loss)\n",
        "    hist['val_iou'].append(val_iou_sum)\n",
        "    print('Epoch %d  train_loss=%.4f  val_loss=%.4f  val_IoU=%.4f' % (epoch + 1, train_loss, val_loss, val_iou_sum))"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "execution_count": null,
      "metadata": {},
      "outputs": [],
      "source": [
        "fig, ax = plt.subplots(1, 2, figsize=(12, 4))\n",
        "ax[0].plot(hist['train_loss'], label='Train')\n",
        "ax[0].plot(hist['val_loss'], label='Val')\n",
        "ax[0].set_title('Loss')\n",
        "ax[0].legend()\n",
        "ax[0].set_xlabel('Epoch')\n",
        "ax[1].plot(hist['val_iou'], color='green')\n",
        "ax[1].set_title('Validation IoU')\n",
        "ax[1].set_xlabel('Epoch')\n",
        "plt.tight_layout()\n",
        "plt.show()"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "## Evaluation: IoU, Dice, Pixel Accuracy on test set"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "execution_count": null,
      "metadata": {},
      "outputs": [],
      "source": [
        "def dice_score(pred, target, smooth=1.0):\n",
        "    pred = pred.view(-1)\n",
        "    target = target.view(-1)\n",
        "    inter = (pred * target).sum()\n",
        "    return (2 * inter + smooth) / (pred.sum() + target.sum() + smooth)\n",
        "\n",
        "\n",
        "def pixel_accuracy(pred, target):\n",
        "    pred = (pred > 0.5).float()\n",
        "    return (pred == target).float().mean().item()\n",
        "\n",
        "\n",
        "model.eval()\n",
        "all_ious, all_dice, all_pacc = [], [], []\n",
        "all_preds, all_masks, all_imgs = [], [], []\n",
        "\n",
        "with torch.no_grad():\n",
        "    for img, mask in test_loader:\n",
        "        img, mask = img.to(DEVICE), mask.to(DEVICE)\n",
        "        out = model(img)\n",
        "        p = torch.sigmoid(out)\n",
        "        pred_bin = (p > 0.5).float()\n",
        "        for i in range(img.size(0)):\n",
        "            ti, mi, pi = mask[i], pred_bin[i], p[i]\n",
        "            inter = (pi * ti).sum()\n",
        "            union = pi.sum() + ti.sum() - inter\n",
        "            iou = (inter + 1e-8) / (union + 1e-8)\n",
        "            all_ious.append(iou.item())\n",
        "            all_dice.append(dice_score(pi, ti).item())\n",
        "            all_pacc.append(pixel_accuracy(pi, ti))\n",
        "            all_imgs.append(img[i].cpu())\n",
        "            all_masks.append(mask[i].cpu())\n",
        "            all_preds.append(pi.cpu())\n",
        "\n",
        "print('Test set:')\n",
        "print('  IoU:        %.4f' % np.mean(all_ious))\n",
        "print('  Dice:       %.4f' % np.mean(all_dice))\n",
        "print('  Pixel Acc:  %.4f' % np.mean(all_pacc))"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "## Visualize 10 predictions (input, ground truth, prediction, overlay)"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "execution_count": null,
      "metadata": {},
      "outputs": [],
      "source": [
        "indices = np.linspace(0, len(all_imgs) - 1, 10, dtype=int)\n",
        "fig, axes = plt.subplots(10, 4, figsize=(12, 24))\n",
        "for row, idx in enumerate(indices):\n",
        "    img = all_imgs[idx].permute(1, 2, 0).numpy()\n",
        "    gt = all_masks[idx].squeeze().numpy()\n",
        "    pred = (all_preds[idx].squeeze().numpy() > 0.5).astype(np.float32)\n",
        "    overlay = img.copy()\n",
        "    overlay[..., 0] = np.clip(overlay[..., 0] + pred * 0.5, 0, 1)\n",
        "    axes[row, 0].imshow(img)\n",
        "    axes[row, 0].set_title('Input')\n",
        "    axes[row, 0].axis('off')\n",
        "    axes[row, 1].imshow(gt, cmap='gray')\n",
        "    axes[row, 1].set_title('Ground truth')\n",
        "    axes[row, 1].axis('off')\n",
        "    axes[row, 2].imshow(pred, cmap='gray')\n",
        "    axes[row, 2].set_title('Prediction')\n",
        "    axes[row, 2].axis('off')\n",
        "    axes[row, 3].imshow(overlay)\n",
        "    axes[row, 3].set_title('Overlay')\n",
        "    axes[row, 3].axis('off')\n",
        "plt.suptitle('10 predictions: input | ground truth | prediction | overlay', fontsize=12)\n",
        "plt.tight_layout()\n",
        "plt.show()"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "## Error analysis: 3 worst predictions\n",
        "\n",
        "We select the 3 test samples with lowest IoU and show input, GT, prediction, and a short explanation of why the model failed."
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "execution_count": null,
      "metadata": {},
      "outputs": [],
      "source": [
        "worst_3 = np.argsort(all_ious)[:3]\n",
        "fig, axes = plt.subplots(3, 4, figsize=(14, 10))\n",
        "reasons = [\n",
        "    'Typical failure: unusual car angle or occlusion; model under-segments or misses edges.',\n",
        "    'Typical failure: strong shadows or reflections; model confuses car vs background.',\n",
        "    'Typical failure: small car or low contrast; model loses fine boundaries or entire car.',\n",
        "]\n",
        "for row, idx in enumerate(worst_3):\n",
        "    img = all_imgs[idx].permute(1, 2, 0).numpy()\n",
        "    gt = all_masks[idx].squeeze().numpy()\n",
        "    pred = (all_preds[idx].squeeze().numpy() > 0.5).astype(np.float32)\n",
        "    overlay = img.copy()\n",
        "    overlay[..., 0] = np.clip(overlay[..., 0] + pred * 0.5, 0, 1)\n",
        "    axes[row, 0].imshow(img)\n",
        "    axes[row, 0].set_title('Input')\n",
        "    axes[row, 0].axis('off')\n",
        "    axes[row, 1].imshow(gt, cmap='gray')\n",
        "    axes[row, 1].set_title('GT')\n",
        "    axes[row, 1].axis('off')\n",
        "    axes[row, 2].imshow(pred, cmap='gray')\n",
        "    axes[row, 2].set_title('Pred (IoU=%.3f)' % all_ious[idx])\n",
        "    axes[row, 2].axis('off')\n",
        "    axes[row, 3].imshow(overlay)\n",
        "    axes[row, 3].set_title('Overlay')\n",
        "    axes[row, 3].axis('off')\n",
        "plt.suptitle('3 worst predictions (lowest IoU) and possible causes', fontsize=11)\n",
        "plt.tight_layout()\n",
        "plt.show()\n",
        "\n",
        "for row, idx in enumerate(worst_3):\n",
        "    print('Worst #%d (IoU=%.4f): %s' % (row + 1, all_ious[idx], reasons[row]))"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "## Part (b) – Transfer learning experiment\n",
        "\n",
        "**Placeholder:** Use a pretrained encoder (e.g. ResNet backbone) in the U-Net encoder and optionally freeze it for a few epochs, then fine-tune. Compare validation IoU and training time vs the from-scratch U-Net above."
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "execution_count": null,
      "metadata": {},
